==English==
===Pronunciation===
*yâ(r)n, /jɑː(r)n/, /<tt>jA:(r)n</tt>/
===Etymology===
From the [[w:Middle English|Middle English,]] from the [[w:Old English|Old English]] ''[[gearn]];'' which is akin to the [[w:Old High German|Old High German]] ''[[garn]],'' which is '''yarn,''' and [[w:Greek language|Greek]] (''chordē''), ''[[string]];'' [[w:Latin language|Latin]] ''[[hernia]],'' that is [[rupture]], and the [[w:Sanskrit language|Sanskrit]] (''hira''), ''[[band]].''

===Noun===
'''yarn''' (uncountable and countable; plural: [[yarns]])

# a twisted strand of fiber used for knitting
# {{nautical}} Bundles of fibers twisted together, and which in turn are twisted in bundles to form [[strand]]s, which in their turn are twisted or [[plait]]ed to form [[rope]].
# a story, a tale

